# Bug Fixes mods for Forge 26.1

These mods fix bugs present in Vanilla Minecraft, other mods, or in loaders.


| Name | Links | Description | Alternatives |
|------|-------|-------------| --------------|
| AttributeFix | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/attributefix) / [MR](https://modrinth.com/mod/attributefix) | Removes arbitrary limits on Minecraft's attribute system. Uable to modify the base attributes of players/mobs, only change the caps. For that functionality, check out our guide [here.](https://modpack-dev-knowledgebase.github.io/modpack-dev-wiki/guide/custom-content/attribute-modification/) | - |
| Max Health Fix | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/max-health-fix) / [MR](https://modrinth.com/mod/max-health-fix) | Fixes an old bug in Minecraft that causes the "Max Health" attribute to be ignored when a player joins the game. | - |
| ModernFix* | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/modernfix) / [MR](https://modrinth.com/mod/modernfix) | All-in-one mod that improves performance, reduces memory usage, and fixes many bugs | - |
| Simple Snowy Fix | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/simple-snowy-fix-forge-fabric) / [MR](https://modrinth.com/mod/simple-snowy-fix-(forge-fabric)) | Fixes incorrect snow generation on tree leaves | - |

\* - A must-have mod for nearly any modpack. Only in very rare circumstances should you not use this mod or an equivalent.

** - Prone to issues or conflicts with other mods